# Generated lockfiles — auto-resolve merge conflicts by keeping the current
# side ("ours"), then let tooling regenerate as needed. Requires a one-time
# per-clone driver registration:  just setup-git-drivers
#
# Rationale: multiple machines/agents (dev boxes, hsb1 direnv, CI) regenerate
# these independently, producing spurious textual conflicts on pull/rebase.
# The lockfiles are deterministic outputs of nix/devenv — never hand-edited —
# so "keep one side, regenerate if stale" is always safe.
devenv.lock merge=ours
flake.lock  merge=ours
